snippet.textDisplay:
Could not relate more to every aspect of this video. Being in a relationship is such a double standard, because one one hand (like you said), you feel as if your independence appears to be owned by someone else. I definitely struggled with this in my last relationship and felt like my individuality didn't belong to me anymore, but rather as a simple building block to the relationship. On the other hand, being single we're taught that we are "more vulnerable," and even though this is often the time where we grow the most and realize the most about ourself, society has a way of deeming being single as "being flawed." Also the fact that single women are constantly looked down upon is ridiculous. I can't count the number of times where family members have made comments like, "you still don't have a boyfriend!?"

Relationships are great when they're great, but they don't complete you and they should never devalue you.
